Package org.sbml.squeezer.gui

This package contains all necessary classes for the graphical user interface.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GeneratorSelectionDialog
    This class implements a dialog which lets the user choose whether they want to create kinetic equations or default function terms in the case that a model is both qualitative (contains transitions) as well as quantitative (contains reactions) (Aug 30, 2020)
    KineticLawGeneratorWorker
    Generates kinetic laws using SwingWorker
    KineticLawSelectionDialog
    This is the main GUI class.
    KineticLawSelectionPanel
    A panel, which contains all possible kinetic equations for the current reaction.
    KineticLawTable
    Creates a table that displays all created kinetic equationns.
    KineticLawTableCellRenderer
    A renderer that paints the background of every second row white or in light blue.
    KineticLawTableModel
    Data model for the KineticLawTable that determins, which information is displayed there and it provides methods to access comlumn or row names and single elements in the table.
    KineticLawWindowAdapter
    This class allows SBMLsqueezer to create a kinetic law interactively for just one reaction.
    LaTeXRenderer
    Provide all needed functions for the latex renderer.
    SBMLsqueezerUI
    The central class for SBMLsqueezer's graphical user interface.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    SBMLsqueezerUI.Command
    This is what the graphical user interface of SBMLsqueezer can do...
